        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 2:58PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 300 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 21 miles west of Henrys Lake to 12 miles north
of Kilgore. Movement was east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Raynolds Pass, Lakeview, and Red Rock Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
